CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 6, 1953, pg. 28, reads: "Repeat Winners - Herron Hill Jr. High School repeated as city track titlist last week at Oliver Field. The victorious Herron Hill squad is shown above.  Front row, left to right, Lebarron Young, George Hamilton, Ralph Proctor, Guy Carter and Phillip Hughes.  Back row, left to right, Leroy Lowry, manager; William Johnson, Robert Easley, Henry Harris, Coach Rugh, John Weston, Allen Goodman, David Gibson and Clarence Rockamore, manager. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Herron Hill track team, from left in back: manager Leroy Lowry, William "Billy" Jackson or Johnson, Robert "Bob" Easley, Henry Harris, Coach Rugh, John Weston, Alan Goode or Goodman, David Gibson, Clarence Rockefeller or Rockamore; front row: LeBarron Young, George Harrison or Hamilton, Ralph Proctor, Jr., Guy Carter, and Phillip "Phil" Hughes
